com.github.anno4j.model.impl.selector

Class TextQuoteSelector

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.anno4j.model.impl.ResourceObject
      • com.github.anno4j.model.Selector
        • com.github.anno4j.model.impl.selector.TextQuoteSelector
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.openrdf.repository.object.RDFObject

    public class TextQuoteSelector
extends Selector
    Conforms to http://www.w3.org/ns/oa#TextQuoteSelector A Selector that describes a textual segment by means of quoting it, plus passages before or after it. For example, if the document were "abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz", one could select "efg" by a oa:prefix of "abcd", the quotation of oa:exact "efg" and a oa:suffix of "hijk". The text MUST be normalized before recording. Each TextQuoteSelector MUST have exactly 1 oa:exact property. Each TextQuoteSelector SHOULD have exactly 1 oa:prefix property, and MUST NOT have more than 1. Each TextQuoteSelector SHOULD have exactly 1 oa:suffix property, and MUST NOT have more than 1.
